Quantum GIS (QGIS) is a Geographic Information System (GIS) that runs on Linux,
Unix, Mac OSX, and Windows. QGIS supports vector, raster, and database formats.
QGIS is licensed under the GNU Public License. 
Some of the major features include: 
Support for spatially enabled PostGIS tables 
Support for shapefiles, ArcInfo coverages, Mapinfo, and other formats 
supported by OGR 
Raster support for a large number of formats 
Identify features 
Display attribute tables 
Select features 
GRASS Digitizing 
Feature labeling 
